Driver license school management system 

Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
Driver License School Management System
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
This document defines the requirements for a Driver License School Management System designed to automate and manage the full lifecycle of learner drivers—from registration to graduation—within an Ethiopian driving school context.
1.2 Scope
The system will:
•	Manage student (learner) registration and enrollment
•	Schedule and manage driving lessons (theoretical & practical)
•	Track student progress and performance
•	Manage instructors and assignments
•	Conduct and record exams (theory & practical)
•	Handle certification and graduation
•	Provide reports for management
2. Overall Description
2.1 Product Perspective
The system is a centralized application (web or desktop) used by driving schools to manage operations efficiently.
2.2 User Classes (Actors)
1. Student / Learner
•	Registers and attends training
•	Takes exams and progresses to licensing
2. Instructor
•	Provides training (theory and practical)
•	Evaluates student performance
3. Supervisor
•	Monitors training quality
•	Oversees instructors and student progress
4. Manager
•	Manages the entire school
•	Handles administration and reporting
3. Case Study Scenario (End-to-End Workflow)
1.	A learner registers in the system
2.	Manager approves registration and assigns learner to a program
3.	Supervisor assigns instructor
4.	Learner attends theory classes
5.	Learner takes theory exam
6.	If passed → proceeds to practical training
7.	Instructor conducts driving sessions
8.	Instructor evaluates learner progress
9.	Learner takes final practical exam
10.	Supervisor validates results
11.	Manager approves graduation
12.	Certificate/license completion recorded
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Student / Learner Functional Requirements
Registration & Profile
•	Register in the system
•	Update personal information
•	Upload required documents (ID, photos)
Training Management
•	View assigned schedule (theory & practical)
•	View instructor details
•	Track training progress
Exam Management
•	Register for theory exam
•	View exam results
•	Register for practical exam
Certification
•	View graduation status
•	Download/print certificate
4.2 Instructor Functional Requirements
Training Delivery
•	View assigned students
•	Manage training schedules
•	Conduct theory and practical sessions
Student Evaluation
•	Record attendance
•	Evaluate student performance
•	Provide feedback
Progress Tracking
•	Update learner progress status
•	Recommend students for exams

4.3 Supervisor Functional Requirements
Monitoring
•	Monitor instructor activities
•	Monitor student progress
Assignment
•	Assign instructors to students
•	Adjust training schedules
Evaluation Oversight
•	Review student performance reports
•	Approve readiness for exams
Quality Control
•	Ensure training standards are met
•	Handle complaints/issues
4.4 Manager Functional Requirements
Administration
•	Manage user accounts (students, instructors, supervisors)
•	Assign roles and permissions
Program Management
•	Create training programs
•	Define course duration and structure
Enrollment
•	Approve student registrations
•	Assign students to programs
Exam Management
•	Schedule theory and practical exams
•	Approve final results
Certification
•	Approve student graduation
•	Issue certificates
Reporting
•	Generate reports:
o	Student enrollment
o	Pass/fail rates
o	Instructor performance
o	Revenue (if applicable)
4.5 General Functional Requirements
•	Secure login/logout
•	Role-based access control
•	Notifications (schedule, exams, results)
•	Search and filtering (students, instructors, reports)
•	Audit logs
5. Non-Functional Requirements
5.1 Performance
•	Response time ≤ 2 seconds
•	Support multiple concurrent users
5.2 Security
•	Secure authentication (encrypted passwords)
•	Role-based authorization
•	Data privacy protection
5.3 Usability
•	Simple and intuitive interface
•	Easy navigation
•	Mobile-friendly design
5.4 Reliability
•	System uptime ≥ 99%
•	Backup and recovery system
5.5 Scalability
•	Support multiple driving school branches
•	Handle large number of learners
5.6 Maintainability
•	Modular architecture
•	Easy updates and enhancements
5.7 Compatibility
•	Web browser support (Chrome, Edge, Firefox)
•	Works on desktop and mobile devices

6. Use Case Summary
Actor	Use Cases
Student	Register, attend training, take exams, graduate
Instructor	Train students, evaluate performance
Supervisor	Assign instructors, monitor progress
Manager	Manage system, approve registrations, generate reports
